<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-first-order-linear" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>First-Order Linear ODEs</title>

  <introduction>
<p>
  We now come to another common family of ODEs: first-order linear differential equations. Just as with separable ODEs, they are
  well understood, and we have a clean way of solving them! We will also see an interesting application to mixing problems,
  which on first pass may seem tricky to set up, but writing them as a first0order linear differential equation
  allows us to tackle these problems. 
</p>
  </introduction>

